<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="593" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,258,1111]" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,258,283]" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Clypeus emarginated at basal margin, with median carina from half of clypeus to supraclypeal area, apical margin nearly truncated; first metasomal segment petiolate, short and thick, T1 with swollen part in dorsal view nearly 1.6 × as long as wide, abruptly widening at one-fourth of the tergum from base, then slightly narrowly to apical margin; T2–T3 with well developed apical lamella, and T4 with apical lamella at only lateral corners.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
