<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="593" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,258,1111]" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,474,499]" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[354,438,475,499]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">Female</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus box="[454,562,474,499]" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">Holotype</typeStatus>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[725,810,475,499]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="593" unit="mm" value="13.0">13 mm</quantity>
; fore wing length 
<quantity box="[1023,1129,475,499]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.23" pageId="4" pageNumber="593" unit="mm" value="12.3">12.3 mm</quantity>
. Structure as in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Discoelius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantiacus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">Discoelius aurantiacus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[292,381,511,534]" pageId="4" pageNumber="593" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but differs as follows. Inner eye margins in frontal view as far apart from each other at vertex as at clypeus. Clypeus in frontal view slightly greater than 1.3 × as wide as long (
<figureCitation box="[1106,1177,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,263,1950,1973]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,555,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1437,555,1929]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 8. Discoelius nigerrimus sp. nov., holotype, ♀. 6. Head, frontal view. 7. Propodeum and metasoma, dorsal view. 8. Metasoma, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261968/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), emarginated at basal margin, with median carina from half of clypeus to supraclypeal area. T 
<quantity box="[958,1000,582,607]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="4" pageNumber="593" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
dorsal view longer than wide, 1.2 × as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[317,388,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,263,1950,1973]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,555,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1437,555,1929]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 8. Discoelius nigerrimus sp. nov., holotype, ♀. 6. Head, frontal view. 7. Propodeum and metasoma, dorsal view. 8. Metasoma, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261968/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). T2–T3 with developed apical lamella (
<figureCitation box="[860,931,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,263,1950,1973]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,555,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1437,555,1929]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 8. Discoelius nigerrimus sp. nov., holotype, ♀. 6. Head, frontal view. 7. Propodeum and metasoma, dorsal view. 8. Metasoma, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261968/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
), and T4 with apical lamella at only lateral corners.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,258,1111]" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis box="[199,269,691,715]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">Color.</emphasis>
Black, with two faint orange marks near anterior margin of pronotum. Propodeal valvulae dark brown. Wings dark brown, strongly infuscate, veins dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,258,1111]" box="[199,389,762,787]" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">
<emphasis box="[199,257,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="593">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
